article.headline: Arizona 75, USC 64
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler scored 20 points and
Shawntinice Polk added 17 in Arizona's 75-64 win over Southern
California on Thursday night.

Aimee Grzyb and Natalie Jones each added 11 for Arizona (13-4,
5-1 Pac-10). Ebony Hoffman led USC (7-7, 4-2) with 17 points, while
Eshaya Murphy had 15.

The Wildcats shot 73 percent (19 of 26) in the first half to
USC's 29 percent, but led only 46-30 at halftime and couldn't seal
the win until the final minutes.

The Wildcats led 69-55 with 5:05 remaining in the game after
Polk's layup. USC scored nine straight to close to within five with
49 seconds left before the Wildcats won with free throws and a
breakaway layin by Natalie Jones.

After Murphy connected on a three-pointer with 4:16 remaining in
the first half to narrow Arizona's lead to 30-28, the Wildcats
scored the final 14 points before the break.

Wheeler scored eight of her 17 first-half points in the late
surge.
